{"type":"message","id":"50243372","parentId":"2abb42b1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:36:40.997Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_so8z6s5p8kyh_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5480\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2867\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 033600 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"clear-rook","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5480\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2867\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 033600 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n","name":"pwsh C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774337800995}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd0457e0","parentId":"50243372","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:36:41.000Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_so8z6s5p8kyh_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 033324\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at my current state and goals, I need to advance the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The next action is to implement a TIC classifier on the pulse log files.\r\n\r\nLet me check what's available:\r\n- Pulse logs are at `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- I need to implement TIC classifier\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nFor a TIC experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Read recent pulse logs\r\n2. Build a simple classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me implement a basic TIC classifier as a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies common patterns (invariants) vs unique content (variants)\r\n3. Makes predictions about next pulse based on invariants\r\n4. Reports accuracy metrics\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 advancement toward COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires implementing a classifier that distinguishes invariant structure from variant content across pulse logs. The pulse logs contain structured patterns (timestamps, section headers, goal updates) that represent causal invariants, while the varying content represents event-driven changes.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/tic_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression experiment by analyzing pulse logs to classify content as invariant (causal structure) or variant (events), then measuring prediction accuracy against the success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$SampleSize = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$startTime = Get-Date\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs sorted by time\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Loading pulse logs (pattern: $LogPattern)...\"\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern | Sort-Object Name -Descending | Select-Object -First $SampleSize\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[TIC] ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs, found $($pulseFiles.Count)\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Loaded $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\n# Define invariant patterns (structural elements that recur)\r\n$InvariantPatterns = @(\r\n    '\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}',           # Timestamps\r\n    '## (Active|Completed|Pending)', # Section headers\r\n    '- \\[ \\]',                       # Unchecked TODO\r\n    '- \\[x\\]',                       # Checked TODO\r\n    '### (OBSERVATION|ACTION|MUTATION)', # Report sections\r\n    '\\$',                           # Dollar amounts\r\n    '^\\d+\\.',                       # Numbered lists\r\n    'Phase \\d',                     # Phase markers\r\n    'λ=',                           # Lambda parameter\r\n    '^\\|'                           # Table rows\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Read all pulse contents\r\n$allPulseContents = @()\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $allPulseContents += @{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\")\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract structural invariants (same section order, headers)\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Extracting structural invariants...\"\r\n$structureFingerprint = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $allPulseContents) {\r\n    $headers = $pulse.Lines | Where-Object { $_ -match '^#+\\s+' }\r\n    foreach ($header in $headers) {\r\n        $key = $header.Trim()\r\n        if (-not $structureFingerprint.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n            $structureFingerprint[$key] = 0\r\n        }\r\n        $structureFingerprint[$key]++\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify each line as invariant (present in >80% of pulses) or variant\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Classifying invariant vs variant content...\"\r\n$invariants = @()\r\n$variants = @()\r\n$totalLines = 0\r\n\r\nforeach ($pulse in $allPulseContents) {\r\n    foreach ($line in $pulse.Lines) {\r\n        $totalLines++\r\n        $trimmed = $line.Trim()\r\n        if ($trimmed.Length -eq 0) { continue }\r\n        \r\n        $isInvariant = $false\r\n        \r\n        # Check if line matches invariant patterns\r\n        foreach ($pattern in $InvariantPatterns) {\r\n            if ($trimmed -match $pattern) {\r\n                $isInvariant = $true\r\n                break\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        # Check if header is structural invariant\r\n        if ($trimmed -match '^#+\\s+' -and $structureFingerprint.ContainsKey($trimmed)) {\r\n            if ($structureFingerprint[$trimmed] -gt ($allPulseContents.Count * 0.8)) {\r\n                $isInvariant = $true\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        if ($isInvariant) {\r\n            $invariants += $trimmed\r\n        } else {\r\n            $variants += $trimmed\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$classificationRate = if ($totalLines -gt 0) { ($invariants.Count + $variants.Count) / $totalLines * 100 } else { 0 }\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Classification Results:\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  - Total lines analyzed: $totalLines\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  - Invariant lines: $($invariants.Count) ($(if($totalLines){[\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:34:07\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774337800997}}
